title: For Sale:  Springfield XD .45 Tactical set up to shoot .45 SUPER
postcontent: Just finished setting this gun up about two months ago, and have shot it quite a bit since. My wife and I are looking at buying a house, so im thining the collection to help fund that. Other wise I would not be selling it. The guns has a number of upgrade parts, some for the basic .45acp configuration, and some for running the .45 SUPER loads I use.Parts that are in the gunPowder River Sear, and Match/Target triggerSpringer precision 1911 guide rod with wolf 24Lb, and 28Lb extra power recoil springsWolff extra power Firing pin spring Wolff extra power Magazine spring in one mag, stock spring in the other (didnt find the mag springs necessary so did change the second one)5.71" Threaded StormLake match stainless barrel with LoneWolf .460 Rowland muzzle break, recontoured for the smaller XD slide. I did this myself, so its not perfect, but does look pretty good. TPA SIG Fully adjustable, white outline, target sights.Parts included with the gunstandard XD 5" barrelStandard hollow recoil spring guidWolff heavy weight Recoil spring guide18Lb stock spring20Lb Wolff extra power spring....This can be used with standard ACP loads, as well as lower end .45Super loads. CMB Razor tactical muzzle brake. This break looks cleaner on the pistol than the LW brake does, but dosent do as good a job at attenuating the recoil generated by top end .45Super loads.Ok so a little history on the pistol, and the reason for the parts etc.Ive owned the gun for a while, and have spent quite a bit of time and energy on it. The pistols fun, accurate, and with the correct loading VERY powerful. The parts ive added are all basicly to duplicate the .460 Rowland, but with a standard .45 ACP chamber, which allows the use of regular ACP rounds without swaping barrels (cause taking off the muzzle breaks is annoying). With the different guids, and springs, the gun can be tailored to run reliably with anything from regular 230 ball rounds at 850 upto (and exceeding, tho i never felt the need), 230s loaded to 1250FPS in the correct .45 super brass. Right now the gun is set up with the LW break and 24# spring, which allows it to comfortably handle all but the weakest .45ACP ammo, as well as what became my standard loadings of 200grn XTPs at 1250 (the 230s didnt seem to work any better and recoiled quite a bit more). I will include my load data, reloading dies, and what components i have left.thanksKeaoREDACTED
